What Its Really Like to Fight for the Is.title: What It's Really Like to Fight for the Islamic State
What Its Really Like to Fight for the Is.description: VICE News has obtained footage taken from the headcam of an Islamic State (IS) fighter who died in March while battling Kurdish peshmerga troops in northern Iraq. The clash took place about 30 miles north of Mosul. Unlike IS propaganda, which often presents sweeping battlefield victories, the video shows chaos, panic, and the fighters retreating.

Second Battle of Donetsk Airport
Ukrainian volunteer recon unit
Ukraine War - Ukrainian Paramilitary In Heavy Intense Helmet Cam Firefight Near Donetsk Airport. Ukrainian forces in heavy combat during firefight fighting action near the Donetsk Airport. The Ukrainian Paramilitary volunteer reconnaissance battalion engaged with novorossian rebels about 4Km away from Donetsk Airport. They came into heavy concant with rebel forces while they where on their mission to sound out the situation around the Airport to prepare an Ukrainian military assault onto the area and retreated shortly after the firefight.
